Functions : A function is reusable block of code. It can be call any where in the program
Reusable code : using an existing code with out writing it every time we need
use the same code by passing different arguments to get the results
JS : keyword - function
python :keyword - def
Parameters - values(variables) which are declared inside the () while defining a functions
Arguments - values which are passed through the parameters
Parameters at the time of calling the function
Syntax:
function greet(name)
ex 1 :
function greet(){
            document.write("Hi Bhavana")
        }
        greet()
        document.write("Hi jeshwitha")
        greet()
        function greet(){
            document.write("Hi Anusha")
        }
        greet()
ex 2:
 function g(name){
            document.write("Hi " + name)
        }
        let name = prompt("Enter your name :")
        g(name)
ex 3:
 function add(n1,n2){
            return n1+n2;
        }
        let n1 = parseInt(prompt("Enter 1st number : "))
        let n2 = parseInt(prompt("Enter 2nd number : "))
        let result= add(n1,n2)
        document.write("Addition of "+n1+" and "+n2+"="+ result)

Anonymous function: A function with out a name, after we create a function without name and we assign it to a variable
ex 1: 
sum = function(n1,n2){
let r = n1+n2
return r
}
document.write(sum(2,3))
